<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-339-799  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 339 799.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  Feb 13 1989 n235 p54(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Fire sparked business for Metropolitan Fiber. (Metropolitan FiberSystems Inc.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Titch, Steven.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Soon after Metropolitan Fiber Systems Inc began operating a bypassnetwork in downtown Chicago, a central office operated by IllinoisBell Telephone Co in Hinsdale, IL, burned down and the publicnetwork lost its long-distance links.andP;  The fire forced waryend-users in Chicago to realize the dangers of relying on only onecompany for access to the national network and also prompted themto approach Metropolitan Fiber for both primary and secondaryaccess to long-distance facilities.andP;  With the onslaught of newbusiness, Metropolitan Fiber has established itself as acompetitive alternative to local operating companies in providingdirect access to long distance carriers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Metropolitan Fiber Systems Inc. (services).andO;Topic:     NetworksFiresDisaster PlanningCommunications Service SuppliersTelecommunicationsBack-Up Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>